<section class="min-h-screen bg-black text-white pt-32 pb-20 px-4 relative overflow-hidden">
    
    <!-- Decorative Background Element -->
    <div class="absolute top-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-full max-w-4xl h-full pointer-events-none opacity-20">
        <div class="w-full h-[500px] bg-gradient-to-b from-[#D4AF37] to-transparent rounded-full blur-[120px]"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto relative z-10">
        
        <!-- Header -->
        <div class="text-center mb-16">
            <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-black text-[#D4AF37] mb-6 brand-font tracking-tighter uppercase">The Platform</h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
                Directives for a sovereign future. We advocate for the structural evolution of the human experience through logic, machine context, and biological integrity.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Agenda Grid: Varied Sizes and Shapes -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 auto-rows-fr">

            <!-- 1. Modernizing Justice (Wide on Desktop) -->
            <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-[#D4AF37] hover:bg-white/5 transition-all duration-500 lg:col-span-2 flex flex-col justify-center">
                <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start md:items-center">
                    <div class="bg-[#D4AF37]/10 p-5 rounded-full text-[#D4AF37] flex-shrink-0">
                        <i class="fas fa-balance-scale-right text-4xl"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3 brand-font">Modernizing Justice</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                            Moving beyond retributive antiquity. We advocate for a justice system built on data-driven restoration and objective truth, removing the "illusory hierarchy" of bias in favor of equitable, high-resolution legal frameworks.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 2. Biological Fidelity (Small Square) -->
            <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-[#20B2AA] hover:bg-white/5 transition-all duration-500 flex flex-col items-center text-center justify-center">
                <div class="bg-[#20B2AA]/10 p-4 rounded-full text-[#20B2AA] mb-4">
                    <i class="fas fa-dna text-3xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2 brand-font">Biological Fidelity</h2>
                <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                    Eliminating substance poisoning to ensure a clear signal. Removing systemic toxins to keep the vessel as pure as the intent.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- 3. Machine Context (Small Square) -->
            <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-[#F4C430] hover:bg-white/5 transition-all duration-500 flex flex-col items-center text-center justify-center">
                <div class="bg-[#F4C430]/10 p-4 rounded-full text-[#F4C430] mb-4">
                    <i class="fas fa-microchip text-3xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2 brand-font">Machine Context</h2>
                <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                    Leveraging AI as a neutral arbiter in human friction, providing context to noise and intervention to irrationality.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- 4. Neural Maximization (Tall Card) -->
            <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-[#FF4500] hover:bg-white/5 transition-all duration-500 lg:row-span-2 flex flex-col justify-center">
                <div class="bg-[#FF4500]/10 p-5 w-fit rounded-full text-[#FF4500] mb-6">
                    <i class="fas fa-brain text-4xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4 brand-font">Neural Maximization</h2>
                <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                    Every human brain deserves its highest potential. We advocate for infrastructure that optimizes cognitive health, learning, and neural plasticity, making "superpowers" an baseline accessible to every individual regardless of origin.
                </p>
                <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-white/10 text-xs text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-widest">
                    Optimization Priority: High
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 5. Post-Addiction Economics (Small Square) -->
            <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-[#9370DB] hover:bg-white/5 transition-all duration-500 flex flex-col items-center text-center justify-center">
                <div class="bg-[#9370DB]/10 p-4 rounded-full text-[#9370DB] mb-4">
                    <i class="fas fa-hand-holding-heart text-3xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2 brand-font">Post-Addiction Economics</h2>
                <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                    Ending the exploitation of the dopamine loop. Pivoting to a value-based economy that rewards growth over dependency.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- 6. Dialogue Towards Utopia (Wide Card) -->
            <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-[#FFD700] hover:bg-white/5 transition-all duration-500 lg:col-span-2 flex flex-col justify-center">
                <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start">
                    <div class="bg-[#FFD700]/10 p-5 rounded-full text-[#FFD700] flex-shrink-0">
                        <i class="fas fa-comments text-3xl"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2 brand-font">Constructive Utopianism</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                            Dialogue is the bridge. We foster a culture of constructive interaction aimed at the "endgame"â€”a society where technology and human spirit converge into a functional, sustainable utopia.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 7. Structural & Cultural Reform (Full Width Footer-Style) -->
            <div class="glass-card p-10 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-white hover:bg-white/5 transition-all duration-500 lg:col-span-3">
                <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-10 items-center">
                    <div class="text-center md:text-left">
                        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4 brand-font">Governmental Evolution</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed text-lg">
                            Reforming the foundation. We demand cultural and governmental shifts that reflect these pillars, transitioning from legacy control systems to modern, transparent, and biologically-aware governance.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-white/10 p-10 rounded-2xl text-white hidden md:block">
                        <i class="fas fa-landmark text-6xl"></i>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

         <!-- 2. ADD MOUNT POINT -->
        <div class="mt-24 mb-12">
            <div id="neuro-model-root"></div>
        </div>

        <!-- 3. ADD RESEARCH SUMMARY (Requested HTML) -->
        <div class="border-t border-white/10 pt-12 mt-12">
            <div class="mb-8">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#D4AF37] uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">Methodology & Calibration</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">
                    This model rejects the "linear harm" fallacy (e.g., "1 drink = 1 day lost") in favor of threshold-based actuarial data sourced from the UK Biobank and PATH studies.
                </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                <!-- Point 1: Alcohol -->
                <div class="p-6 rounded-lg bg-white/5 border border-white/10">
                    <h4 class="text-white font-bold mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                        <i class="fas fa-wine-glass text-[#D4AF37]"></i> The 100g Threshold
                    </h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
                        Data from 599,912 drinkers establishes that mortality risk is effectively neutral below 100g of alcohol/week (<7 standard drinks). The model applies zero mortality penalty below this line, but calculates hippocampal atrophy (Memory) beginning at moderate dosages.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Point 2: Tobacco -->
                <div class="p-6 rounded-lg bg-white/5 border border-white/10">
                    <h4 class="text-white font-bold mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                        <i class="fas fa-smoking text-[#FF4500]"></i> Log-Linear Shock
                    </h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
                        Unlike alcohol, cardiovascular damage from smoking saturates rapidly. Smoking 1 cigarette/day confers nearly 50% of the heart disease risk of smoking 20/day. The model applies a "shock penalty" to the Energy metric immediately upon introduction of combustible tobacco.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Point 3: Vaping -->
                <div class="p-6 rounded-lg bg-white/5 border border-white/10">
                    <h4 class="text-white font-bold mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                        <i class="fas fa-cloud text-blue-400"></i> Vascular Stiffness
                    </h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
                        While vaping eliminates ~95% of carcinogens (Cancer Risk), it maintains ~80% of the arterial stiffness (Vascular Age) of smoking due to nicotine-induced vasoconstriction. The model reflects this by sparing "Lifespan" but penalizing "Energy" and "Focus" significantly.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="mt-8 text-[10px] text-gray-600 font-mono">
                SOURCES: Wood et al. (2018) "Risk thresholds for alcohol consumption"; UK Biobank Longitudinal Cohort (N=36,678); Population Assessment of Tobacco and Health (PATH) Wave 1-4.
            </div>
        </div>


        <!-- Call to Action -->
        <div class="mt-20 text-center">
            <h3 class="text-2xl text-white font-bold mb-6">Align with the Movement</h3>
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-center gap-4">
                <a href="/contact" class="btn-gold px-8 py-4 rounded text-lg shadow-[0_0_20px_rgba(212,175,55,0.3)]">
                    Join the Mission
                </a>
                <a href="/merch" class="btn-outline px-8 py-4 rounded text-lg">
                    Represent the Platform
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>
</section>

